    <h1>TIME&#xAD;LINE OF EVENTS</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200825/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-25"><time>2020-08-25</time></a>
        - <span>HOME</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Oc­to­ber 2007 to De­cem­ber 2011: Ms Noor Azlin Ab­dul Rahman vis­its Changi Gen­eral Hospi­tal (CGH) be­cause of chest pains and lung-re­lated is­sues. April 2010: Ra­di­o­log­i­cal re­port rec­om­mends fol­low-up, but it is not done.</p>
    <p>July 2011: Ra­di­o­log­i­cal re­port rec­om­mends fol­low-up, but it is not done. Court later finds Ms Azlin is suf­fer­ing from stage 1 lung can­cer at this point. Fe­bru­ary 2012: Is di­ag­nosed with lung can­cer. March 2012: Un­der­goes surgery to re­move part of right lung, found to have stage 2A lung can­cer. Starts chemo­ther­apy.</p>
    <p>Au­gust 2014: Has a re­lapse; biopsy con­firms stage 4 can­cer.</p>
    <p>Jan­uary 2015: Sues CGH and three doc­tors for de­lay in di­ag­no­sis.</p>
    <p>Fe­bru­ary 2018: High Court dis­misses case.</p>
    <p>Fe­bru­ary 2019: Court of Ap­peal finds CGH neg­li­gent for fail­ing to put in place a sys­tem for proper fol­low-up of ra­di­o­log­i­cal re­sults and pa­tient man­age­ment. April 1, 2019: Ms Azlin dies. Aug 24, 2020: Hear­ing to as­sess damages to be paid to fam­ily starts in High Court.</p>


